title: Grant Hackett is missing after accusing brother of assault
text: Grant Hackett FOUND by police and says he 'doesn't want anything to do with his family' - as his father says he was 'ready for the worst' after a tense phone call earlier in the day Grant Hackett has been located by police in Queensland on Thursday evening Olympic star had been missing since 7.30am on Thursday, his father said He was reportedly last seen at the Palazzo Versace hotel on the Gold Coast His family pleaded with the public to help find the 36-year-old Olympian Just hours before he posted a photo to social media showing a swollen black eye Hackett claimed his brother had beaten him and described him as 'angry' Olympic swimmer was arrested on Wednesday afternoon at his parents' home He was released hours later without charge and is seeking rehab treatment Published: 22:32 GMT, 15 February 2017 | Updated: 08:26 GMT, 16 February 2017 363 shares
